is it possible is it possible to get pregnant if your tubes were tied for seven years without getting them reversed sorry if this isn't the right terms i know they have more complicated names for them i just don't know what they are about out of women will get pregnant during the first years after their tubes are tied an egg has less chance of slipping through if you have your tubes closed by cauterization or burning if you do become pregnant be sure to see your doctor right away there's an increased risk that the egg will be implanted in your fallopian tubes or abdomen rather than in your uterus which can pose a dangerous risk for you to answer your question it is possible to become pregnant after having tubal ligation nothing is fool proof unless you have a total hysterectomy i hope this was helpful take care Ectopic pregnancy Sterilization (surgical procedure) Pregnancy In vitro fertilisation Ovarian cancer Infertility Obstetrics Gonorrhoea Endometriosis Birth control Pelvic inflammatory disease Gynaecology Emergency contraception Urinary incontinence Miscarriage Prostate cancer Premature birth Androgen insensitivity syndrome Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Sexual reproduction Chlamydia Sex reassignment surgery female-to-male Endometrial cancer Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Ovulation Uterus Caesarean section Female reproductive system (human) Spina bifida Oral contraceptive Ovary Endoscopy Prenatal diagnosis Twin Breech birth Childbirth Intersex surgery Human cloning Fetal development Folic acid Intravenous therapy Sexual intercourse Friends Adjustable gastric band Psoriasis Stroke Breastfeeding Fertility awareness Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Abortion debate Homosexuality and medical science Gastroparesis Swyer syndrome Cervical cancer Hysterectomy Earring Intersexuality Prolapse Sexual differentiation Vaginal bleeding Pneumonia Cancer Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Stomach cancer Professional wrestling holds Anal sex Intact dilation and extraction Chicken